# can.word — the grant. Can hands a word to a being. Descends from word.word, being.word, name.word.
# Grounds the getWord shape (seed/present/word/wordStore.js, 10.md §2). A word is a FOLD of
# declare-word facts, not a registry entry. A composite word, a role, carries a
# can of granted words, and words stack. Disable is a new fact, off not gone. `disable` is grounded
# here. Language is no exception to fact, fold, story.

Can grants a word to a being.
A being has the words it can.
A role is a composite word, a can of words. It has no act of its own. The words it grants do.
To grant a role is to grant a word, for a role is a word. One word or many, the grant is the same.
A word can be made of words. Words stack.
A word is declared, a fact, and folds from its declarations, the last the truth.
To disable a word is a new fact. It is off, not gone, until a word declares it again.
